    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a great point about the danger of the state claiming infallibility. it feels like the most consistent logic is that any attempt at \"truth regulation\" is inherently an attempt at control. even if people think they're doing it for good intentions, it's still a fundamental violation of individual liberty. do you think there's any way for a government to actually regulate the internet without becoming essentially an engine of censorship?",
